Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the @puff pastry sheet{1} from your
fridge. Pop the @diced butternut squash{300%g} onto a large #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} then
toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast
on the top shelf until starting to turn soft and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the
@garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the
@chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a
large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, cook the onion until softened,
~{6-8%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @harissa paste{50%g} and cook for
~{1%minute} more.

Add the @water{150%ml} for the sauce and @vegetable stock paste{10%g} to the
onion pan and bring to a simmer. Cook until reduced slightly,
~{5-6%minutes}. Meanwhile, crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g} into
chunks.

Once the sauce has reduced, add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at
a time and stir until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the
chickpeas, Greek style salad cheese and cooked butternut squash. Taste and add
more salt and pepper if needed.

Transfer the butternut squash mixture to an ovenproof #baking dish{}
(we use a 20cm x 20cm dish for 2 people). Cover with the puff pastry, trimming
off any excess. Press some of the pastry over the side of the dish if you can,
or just sit it on top. Make a small hole in the middle - this allows the steam
to escape.

> Tip: Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown,
~{15-20%minutes}.

While the pie is in the oven, do any washing up. Once cooked, leave the pie to
stand for ~{2%minutes}, then divide between plates.

-- Broccoli Addition (Optional) --

If you've chosen to add @?broccoli florets{200%g} to your meal, put the pie in
the oven then bring a medium #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}.
When the pie has 5 minutes cooking time remaining, add the broccoli to the
boiling water and cook until just tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Drain in a
#colander{}. Serve with the pie.